window.__QUIZ_DATA__=[{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>1","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION AGE : HISTORY OF COMPUTERS","question":"The Stepped Reckoner was developed by","images":[],"options":{"A":"Gottfied Leibinitz","B":"Herman Hollerith","C":"John Von Neumann","D":"William Schickard"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The Stepped Reckoner was developed by Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz, a German mathematician and philosopher, in the late 17th century. It was a mechanical calculator that used a stepped drum, known as the Leibniz wheel, to perform arithmetic operations. Leibniz built two Stepped Reckoners, one in 1694 and one in 1706.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>2","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"The binary number 1001012 can be written in denary as","images":[],"options":{"A":"25","B":"37","C":"45","D":"211"},"answer":"B","explanation":"1001012 = 1 \u00d7 25 + 0 \u00d7 24 + 0 \u00d7 23 + 1 \u00d7 22 + 0 \u00d7 21 + 1 \u00d7 20    = (1 \u00d7 32) + (0 \u00d7 16) + (0 \u00d7 8) + (1 \u00d7 4) + (0 \u00d7 2) + (1 \u00d7 1)    = 32 + 0 + 0 + 4 + 0 + 1     = 37","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>3","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION AGE : DATA AND INFORMATION","question":"The first stage in computer data processing procedure is","images":[],"options":{"A":"collection of data","B":"communication of information","C":"conversion of data","D":"manipulation of data"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The first stage in the computer data processing procedure is indeed the collection of data. This involves gathering raw data from various sources, such as user input, sensors, files, or databases.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>4","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION AGE : DATA AND INFORMATION","question":"One advantage of electronic data processing is that it","images":[],"options":{"A":"involves special skill","B":"deals only with simple data","C":"is completely error-free","D":"handles complex data"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Electronic data processing (EDP) offers several advantages, including:    - Ability to handle large volumes of complex data quickly and accurately  - Automation of repetitive tasks  - Improved data security and integrity  - Enhanced decision-making capabilities  - Increased productivity and efficiency    EDP enables organizations to process complex data, such as numerical calculations, data analysis, and simulations, with speed and accuracy. This has revolutionized various industries, including finance, healthcare, and science.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>5","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : CLASSIFICATION OF COMPUTERS","question":"The type of computer that has the ability of counting in discrete form is referred to as","images":[],"options":{"A":"analogue computer","B":"digital computer","C":"hybrid computer","D":"versatile computer"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A digital computer is a type of computer that processes information in discrete form, using binary digits (bits) to represent data. It can only understand and process discrete values, like 0s and 1s, and is designed to perform calculations and logical operations on this discrete data.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>6","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : APPLICATION OF ICT IN EVERYDAY LIFE","question":"One reason for using Computer Aided Design in manufacturing is that","images":[],"options":{"A":"it uses few system resources","B":"manufacturing time is reduced","C":"designers do not need training to use it","D":"3D designs are easily produced with it"},"answer":"B","explanation":"One of the primary reasons for using Computer-Aided Design (CAD) in manufacturing is to reduce manufacturing time. CAD software allows designers to create and modify designs digitally, which can significantly speed up the design process. This, in turn, can lead to faster product development and reduced time-to-market. Additionally, CAD can help to identify potential design flaws and manufacturing issues early on, which can further reduce manufacturing time and costs.    \"3D designs are easily produced with it\" is true, but the primary advantage relevant to manufacturing is the reduction in time, making \"manufacturing time is reduced\" the most accurate answer.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>7","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : INTERNET~~INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : PROCESS OF INFORMATION TRANSMISSION","question":"Which one of the following statements is true about Voice Over IP? It","images":[],"options":{"A":"converts voice and video data into a digital signal and transfers it over the Internet","B":"converts voice and video data into a digital signal and broadcasts it via a transmitter","C":"is a voice over communication system which is cyber-attack proof","D":"is a circuit-switched data communication system"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Converts voice and video data signal into a digital signal and transfers it over the Internet.    Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) is a technology that converts analog voice and video signals into digital data packets and transmits them over the Internet. This allows for real-time communication, such as voice and video calls, to be made over the Internet.    VoIP offers several benefits, including:    - Cost-effective communication  - Increased mobility and flexibility  - Enhanced features and functionality  - Scalability and adaptability","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>8","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"BASIC COMPUTING : COMPONENTS OF COMPUTERS~~INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"Which one of the following sets of devices can be used to store data during processing?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Cache, RAM and Register","B":"Cache, Register and ROM","C":"Flash Drive, ROM and Hard Disk Drive","D":"RAM, Register and Zip Drive"},"answer":"A","explanation":"During processing, data is temporarily stored in:    1. Registers: Small amounts of data are stored in processor registers for quick access and processing.  2. RAM (Random Access Memory): Data is stored in RAM for rapid access and processing. RAM is volatile, meaning data is lost when power is turned off.  3. Cache: A small, fast memory within the processor that stores frequently accessed data to reduce access time.    These three options (Cache, RAM, and Register) are used to store data during processing.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>9","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION AGE : DATA AND INFORMATION~~INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"The process of inspecting, transforming and modeling data to get useful information is known as","images":[],"options":{"A":"collation","B":"interpretation","C":"execution","D":"analysis"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Data analysis is the process of inspecting, transforming, and modeling data to extract useful information, patterns, and insights. It involves various techniques, such as:    1. Data cleaning and preprocessing  2. Data visualization  3. Statistical analysis  4. Machine learning  5. Data mining    The goal of data analysis is to turn raw data into actionable information, supporting decision-making, problem-solving, and business intelligence.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>10","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION PROCESSING : THE ART OF INFORMATION PROCESSING","question":"One disadvantage of using computer for information processing is","images":[],"options":{"A":"need for staff retraining","B":"increased running cost in the long run","C":"the increase in storage space","D":"redundancy of computers in the long run"},"answer":"A","explanation":"One of the primary disadvantages of using computers for information processing is the need for staff retraining. When organizations adopt new computer systems or software, employees often require training to learn how to use these systems effectively. This can be time-consuming, costly, and may temporarily reduce productivity as staff adapt to the new technology.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>11","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : PROCESS OF INFORMATION TRANSMISSION","question":"The diagram in the Figure 1 illustrates a process called","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"information processing","B":"information transmission","C":"modulation","D":"synchronization"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Information transmission is the process of sending data from one point to another. It's the foundation of modern communication, enabling everything from simple phone calls to complex global networks.    Key Components and Processes  Encoding: Converting information into a digital format that can be transmitted.  Transmission Medium: The channel used to send the data. This could be a physical cable (like Ethernet), wireless signals (like Wi-Fi), or even light (like fiber optics).  Modulation: The process of encoding information onto a carrier signal, making it suitable for transmission over a specific medium.  Demodulation: The reverse process of extracting information from the carrier signal at the receiving end.  Decoding: Converting the received digital data back into its original format.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>12","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : MEDIUM OF INFORMATION TRANSMISSION","question":"The transmitter in communication is the component that","images":[],"options":{"A":"decodes sender's signal by interpretation","B":"encodes interpreted data by using machine language","C":"broadcasts synchronous signals","D":"launches signal into the air"},"answer":"D","explanation":"In communication systems, the transmitter is responsible for converting the information (usually in the form of electrical signals) into a form that can be transmitted over a communication medium. This often involves modulating the signal and then launching it into the air as radio waves (in the case of wireless communication) or through a wired medium.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>13","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : PROCESS OF INFORMATION TRANSMISSION","question":"Which of the following resources is not usually shared in a network?","images":[],"options":{"A":"VGA projector","B":"Laserjet printer","C":"Folder","D":"File"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The correct answer is: VGA projector.    Explanation:    VGA projectors are usually not shared over a network because they are hardware devices used for displaying visual content directly from a computer or other media device. They are connected physically to a single computer and not accessible over a network.    \"Laserjet printer\" is often shared in a network so that multiple users can print documents from different devices.    \"Folder\" is commonly shared over a network to allow multiple users to access, store, or edit files within the folder.    \"File\" can also be shared across a network, allowing users to access and collaborate on documents or other types of files.    Thus, VGA projector is the resource that is not usually shared in a network.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>14","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : NETWORKING","question":"Factors to be considered when creating a backup system in a computer network include","images":[],"options":{"A":"amount of RAM, amount of data and time of backup","B":"amount of RAM, amount of data and frequency of backup","C":"media to use, amount of data and frequency of backup","D":"media to use, type of data and time of backup"},"answer":"C","explanation":"When creating a backup system in a computer network, the following factors should be considered:    - Media to use: The type of storage media to use for backups, such as external hard drives, tapes, or cloud storage.  - Amount of data: The total amount of data to be backed up, which determines the storage capacity required.  - Frequency of backup: How often backups should be performed, which depends on the importance of the data and how frequently it changes.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>15","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : INTERNET","question":"The URL www.exams.edu.ng represents the website of","images":[],"options":{"A":"an examination body","B":"a Nigerian-based learning institution","C":"an educational institution in Niger","D":"a research institution in Niger"},"answer":"B","explanation":"The top-level domain \".edu.ng\" indicates an educational institution in Nigeria. The \".ng\" is the country code top-level domain (ccTLD) for Nigeria, and \".edu\" is used for educational institutions. Therefore, a URL with \".edu.ng\" generally represents a website of an educational institution based in Nigeria.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>16","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : INTERNET~~INFORMATION TRANSMISSION : MEDIUM OF INFORMATION TRANSMISSION","question":"The Post Office Protocol (POP) is used to","images":[],"options":{"A":"interconnect devices on the Internet","B":"retrieve email from a mail server","C":"transfer file from a server to a client","D":"send email from one user to another"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Post Office Protocol (POP) is a protocol used to retrieve email from a mail server to a local email client, such as a desktop or mobile email app. It allows users to download their email from the server to their local device for viewing and management.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>17","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : OPERATING SYSTEM","question":"A user working on a computer that is running on Windows 7 issued the command \"Crtl + Alt + Del\" while typing a document. What interface is expected to be displayed on the screen","images":[],"options":{"A":"Restart Windows","B":"Shut Down Windows","C":"Windows Security","D":"Windows Task Manager"},"answer":"D","explanation":"When a user presses \"Ctrl + Alt + Del\" on a Windows 7 computer, the Windows Task Manager will appear. This shortcut is used to open the Task Manager, which allows users to:    - View running processes and applications  - End tasks or processes  - Switch between users  - Lock the computer  - Log off","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>18","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : WORD PROCESSING","question":"Header and Footer are added to a document in Ms Word by just clicking on the","images":[],"options":{"A":"Edit menu","B":"Format menu","C":"Insert menu","D":"View menu"},"answer":"C","explanation":"In Microsoft Word, you can add headers and footers to a document by following these steps:    1. Click on the \"Insert\" menu.  2. Select \"Header\" or \"Footer\" from the drop-down menu.  3. Choose the desired header or footer style from the gallery.  4. Edit the header or footer content as needed.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>19","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : WORD PROCESSING","question":"A typist positioned the insertion point at the beginning of a line of text in a word processor and then pressed down the Shift key and clicked at the opposite end of the text. What would be the result of this action? The text will be","images":[],"options":{"A":"copied into the clipboard","B":"cut into the clipboard","C":"deleted from the storage","D":"highlighted on the screen"},"answer":"D","explanation":"When you press the Shift key and click at the opposite end of the text, it selects or highlights all the text between the insertion point and the point where you clicked. This is known as \"shift-click\" selection.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>20","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : SPREADSHEET","question":"The Microsoft Excel menu bar icon shown in Figure 2 is used to","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"automatically add up selected values","B":"create label that spans multiple columns","C":"spot trends and patterns in user's data using bars, columns and icons","D":"organize data for easy analysis"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The figure above is the Sort & Filter icon. The tools are used for organizing and managing data.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>21","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : SPREADSHEET","question":"To add a new column to the right of the IGR column on the interface in Figure 3, the user would","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"right-click on the cell C1 and then click on insert","B":"right-click on the cell D1 and then click insert","C":"right-click on column C and then click insert","D":"right-click on column D and then click insert"},"answer":"B","explanation":"To add a new column to the right of the IGR column in an Excel workbook:    - Select the column to the right of the IGR column.  - Right-click the selected column header.  - Choose Insert from the context menu.    A new column will appear to the right of the IGR column.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>22","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : RELATIONAL MODEL~~TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"The function of a foreign key in a database is to","images":[],"options":{"A":"uniquely identify tuples in a table","B":"provide a link between data in two tables","C":"uniquely identify an entity occurrence","D":"uniquely identify each record in a table"},"answer":"B","explanation":"A foreign key is a field in a table that references the primary key of another table, establishing a relationship between the two tables. It allows you to link data between tables, enabling queries and joins to retrieve related data.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>23","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : RELATIONAL MODEL~~TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"Use  Figure 4  to answer questions  23  and  24.      How many primary keys exist in figure 4?","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"3","B":"4","C":"5","D":"12"},"answer":"A","explanation":"A primary key is a unique identifier for a record in a table, and it is defined at the column level. A column can be designated as the primary key, ensuring that each value in that column is unique and identifies a single record.    The primary keys are \"CustomerId\" from \"Customers\" table, \"OrderId\" from \"Orders\" table, and \"ProductId\" from \"Products\" table.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>24","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : RELATIONAL MODEL~~TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"Use  Figure 4  to answer questions  23  and  24.    Which of the following contains the primary keys in Figure 4?","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"Customers, Orders and Products","B":"CustomerId, OrderId and ProductId","C":"CustomerId, FirstName, LastName and DateCreated","D":"Customers, CustomerId, FirstName, LastName and DateCreated"},"answer":"A","explanation":"A primary key is a unique identifier for a record in a table, and it is defined at the column level. A column can be designated as the primary key, ensuring that each value in that column is unique and identifies a single record.    The primary keys are \"CustomerId\" from \"Customers\" table, \"OrderId\" from \"Orders\" table, and \"ProductId\" from \"Products\" table.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>25","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : WEB DESIGN PACKAGES","question":"Web Design packages include the following except","images":[],"options":{"A":"Macromedia Dreamweaver","B":"iWeb","C":"Front Page","D":"Adobe Pagemaker"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Pagemaker is a desktop publishing software tool that was used for creating and designing print materials like brochures, magazines, and books. It's not a web design tool, so it's the correct answer.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>26","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : GRAPHIC PACKAGES","question":"The part labelled IV in Figure 5 is used to","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"shape objects","B":"select and transform objects","C":"draw lines and curves","D":"create texts"},"answer":"C","explanation":"The icon is the \"curved tool\" in CorelDraw.    The Curved Tool in CorelDRAW is a versatile tool used to create and edit curved lines and shapes. It offers a variety of options for customizing the shape and appearance of your curves.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>27","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : MAINTENANCE OF COMPUTER","question":"One precautionary measure taken when cleaning a monitor is","images":[],"options":{"A":"covering the monitor with antiglare","B":"cleaning the monitor with alcohol","C":"unplugging the power supply cable","D":"using a vacuum cleaner to dust the monitor casing"},"answer":"C","explanation":"When cleaning a monitor, it's important to unplug the power supply cable to avoid any accidental start-ups or electrical shocks. This precautionary measure ensures your safety while cleaning the monitor.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>28","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : COMPUTER ETHICS","question":"Which one of the following practices is considered ethical","images":[],"options":{"A":"Gaining access into school database to change ones's grades","B":"Gaining access into government database to alter personal details","C":"Logging into a friend's social media account to read inbox messages","D":"Signing into school e-library to read e-books"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The other options involve unauthorized access to private information or systems, which is a violation of privacy and security. Reading e-books from a school e-library is generally considered acceptable as it is within the intended use of the library's resources.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>29","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : SAFETY MEASURES","question":"Proper network implementation and good ICT policies are types of","images":[],"options":{"A":"adaptive measures","B":"corrective measures","C":"perfective measures","D":"preventive measures"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Proper network implementation and good ICT policies are proactive measures taken to prevent potential security threats, data breaches, or technical issues. They aim to prevent problems from occurring in the first place, rather than reacting to them after they've happened.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>30","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : SAFETY MEASURES","question":"Preventive maintenance measures in the computer room include the following options except","images":[],"options":{"A":"good ventilation","B":"proper illumination","C":"the use of rugs","D":"the use of tiles"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Preventive maintenance measures in a computer room aim to ensure a safe and reliable operating environment. While good ventilation and proper illumination are essential, the use of rugs is not recommended as they can generate dust and create a fire hazard.    Instead, floors are typically covered with tiles or other static-dissipative materials to reduce the risk of static electricity damage to sensitive equipment.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>31","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : SAFETY MEASURES","question":"Measures taken to avoid eye strain include the following except","images":[],"options":{"A":"adjusting the brightness of the monitor","B":"adjusting the height of the screen","C":"blinking of eyes often","D":"relaxing the body regularly"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The correct answer is: relaxing the body regularly.    Relaxing the body is generally good for overall health but is not directly related to preventing eye strain.  Adjusting the brightness of the monitor, adjusting the height of the screen, and blinking of eyes often are specific actions that help reduce eye strain during computer use.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>32","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"A database administrator is responsible for the following tasks except","images":[],"options":{"A":"controlling and monitoring user access to the database","B":"enrolling users and maintaining system security","C":"maintaining archived data","D":"maintaining connection between local network and the Internet"},"answer":"D","explanation":"A database administrator (DBA) is responsible for managing and ensuring the performance, security, and integrity of a database. Their tasks include:    Controlling and monitoring user access to the database: Managing user privileges, access levels, and authentication.    Enrolling users and maintaining system security: Creating user accounts, managing passwords, and ensuring database security.    Maintaining archived data: Managing backup and recovery processes, storing and retrieving archived data.    However, maintaining the connection between the local network and the Internet is the responsibility of a network administrator, not a database administrator.    Other tasks that a DBA may perform include:    - Designing and implementing database structures  - Optimizing database performance  - Ensuring data consistency and integrity  - Troubleshooting database issues  - Updating and patching database software","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>33","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : COMPUTER VIRUS","question":"A computer virus replicates itself into other programs on certain areas on the disk during the","images":[],"options":{"A":"dormant phase","B":"execution phase","C":"propagation phase","D":"trigger phase"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A computer virus replicates itself into other programs or areas of the disk during the propagation phase. This is the stage where the virus spreads and infects other parts of the system.    Here's a brief overview of the different phases of a computer virus:    Dormant phase: The virus remains inactive and hides in the system, waiting for a trigger to activate it.    Execution phase: The virus is executed and starts to run its malicious code.    Propagation phase: The virus replicates itself and spreads to other areas of the system or network.    Trigger phase: The virus is triggered to activate and start its malicious activities.    It's important to note that not all viruses follow this exact sequence, and some may have additional phases or variations on these phases.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>34","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES : COMPUTER VIRUS","question":"A malware that copies and replicates itself using computer network and security flaws is","images":[],"options":{"A":"Rootkit virus","B":"Spyware","C":"Trojan Horse","D":"Worm"},"answer":"D","explanation":"A worm is a type of malware that can copy and replicate itself using computer network and security flaws, without needing to be sent as an attachment or downloaded. Worms exploit vulnerabilities in operating systems or applications to spread from system to system, often causing harm and consuming system resources.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>35","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : RELATIONAL MODEL~~TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"The entities in Figure 6 are named","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"RegNo, Name and Age","B":"Musa, Uche and Bayo","C":"Student and Subject","D":"Maths, Eng and DP"},"answer":"C","explanation":"In the context of database design and entity-relationship modeling (ERM), an entity refers to a concept or object that has existence and significance in the real world, not necessarily a table.    In a database, an entity is often represented as a table, but the entity itself is the conceptual object, not the table.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>36","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"TOOLS FOR PROCESSING INFORMATION : DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM","question":"Which one of the following statements is true about database tables?","images":[],"options":{"A":"All the tables in a database have a common name","B":"A table may contain repeating groups","C":"Entries in a column are different from domains based on data type","D":"There are no duplicate rows in a table"},"answer":"D","explanation":"There are no duplicate rows in a table is a true statement as relational database tables are designed to ensure that each row is unique. This uniqueness is often enforced by primary keys or unique constraints.     Duplicate rows can lead to inconsistencies and errors in the data.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>37","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : FILE ORGANIZATION","question":"The major difference between serial and sequential files is that sequential files are","images":[],"options":{"A":"given a key","B":"sorted in a particular order","C":"sorted as they come","D":"recorded in any storage medium"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Sequential files are organized in a specific order, such as alphabetical or numerical order, whereas serial files are not necessarily sorted in any particular order.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>38","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : FILE ORGANIZATION","question":"Which one of the following pairs contains computer file classification?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Master file and Serial file","B":"Random file and Master file","C":"Reference file and Random file","D":"Transaction file and Master file"},"answer":"D","explanation":"In computer file classification, files are usually categorized into two main types:    1. Master file: A permanent file that contains relatively stable data, such as customer information, product catalogs, or employee records. Master files are updated periodically and serve as a reference for other files.  2. Transaction file: A temporary file that contains data related to a specific transaction or event, such as sales orders, payment records, or inventory updates. Transaction files are typically used to update master files.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>39","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : DATABASE SECURITY","question":"Which of the following statements support the goals of data backup?    I. Need for duplication  II. Need for future reference  III. Protection against data loss","images":[],"options":{"A":"I and II only","B":"I and III only","C":"II and III only","D":"I, II and III"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Data backup goals are supported by all three statements:    I. Need for duplication: Backing up data creates a duplicate copy, ensuring that important files are not lost if the original is damaged or destroyed.    II. Need for future reference: Backed-up data can be used for future reference, such as auditing, historical analysis, or recovering previous versions of files.    III. Protection against data loss: The primary goal of data backup is to protect against data loss due to various threats, such as hardware failure, software corruption, human error, or natural disasters.    Data backup is essential for ensuring data availability, integrity, and recoverability. By duplicating data, storing it securely, and maintaining historical versions, backups support all three goals.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Data Processing>2024>40","subject":"Data Processing","year":"2024","type":"Objective","topic":"DATA MANAGEMENT : PARALLEL AND DISTRIBUTED DATABASES","question":"Which of the following characteristics is associated with the architecture of parallel database?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Communication cost and problems cannot be ignored","B":"Machines can be far from each other","C":"Machines are physically close to each other","D":"It is usually associated with shared-nothing architecture"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Parallel databases are designed to distribute data and processing across multiple machines to improve performance and scalability.    A shared-nothing architecture is a common approach in parallel databases, where each node has its own independent memory and storage. This architecture minimizes communication overhead and improves fault tolerance, making it well-suited for large-scale data processing applications.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"}];